    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling core, anchored by **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (78.22) and **Jackson Merrill** (74.69). **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** is our premier start, benefiting from a favorable matchup against Bello and a significant boost from his elite 31-PA BvP history, while **Jackson Merrill** leverages a high-leverage leadoff spot against Taillon to maximize his counting stat potential. **Kyle Tucker** (73.24) and **Jacob Wilson** (72.74) also provide elite production, with **Jacob Wilson**\u2019s projected leadoff status providing the necessary floor to capitalize on the park factors against Wacha. Keep a close eye on **Josh Lowe** (72.21); while his base projection is modest, his specific matchup against Fedde\u2014coupled with a high-probability SB environment due to the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery\u2014makes him a sneaky high-upside play for our scarcity-driven strategy.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involved **Miguel Vargas** (58.56), who was the first player left off the active card. While **Miguel Vargas** showed solid indicators against Kikuchi, he ultimately fell short of the threshold set by **Marcell Ozuna** (61.53) and **Josh Jung** (61.43), both of whom offered superior alignment between their lineup spots and pitcher profiles. We are navigating a few situational red flags: **Heliot Ramos** (48.04) faces a 40% rain risk in his contest against S\u00e1nchez, which could truncate his production or lead to a delay. Additionally, with **Gunnar Henderson** already confirmed as a rainout, we have adjusted our depth to ensure we are not holding dead weight in the lineup. As always, we are monitoring the status of **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Jordan Westburg** to ensure we remain optimal for the remainder of the week.",
